items.text: Try the kidney and liver mee sua! It's awesome!
Can try chicken wing and satay at Chong Pang store. Nice nice
The sardine currypuff here is super delicious!
Mei mei claypot doesn't tasted as what the tips were given. Claypot doesn't even have crust in it at all. Defeats the purpose!
Must try. The morning session wanton mee.
Don't bother to eat from M M BBQ . Long queue and not nice.
Aliff Nasi Lemak.  Close on Friday.   Must try.  Better then changi village.
The chicken chop and ba chor mee are good too
Must try roti john #01-12
Tasty Teo Chew Fish Ball Noodle
Tasty Noodle
Try the nasi lemak @ Aliff Nasi Lemak (stall no. 01-19) variety of accompaniments to choose from
The 01-39 seafood not bad come and try it!!
The aliff nasi lemak stall serves DELICIOUS nasi lemak! Try it!
Pig's kidney mee sua is quite famous here
DON'T ever pack (takeaway) the satay from the Malay stall (facing the main road)at Kaki bukit market and hawker centre. I was shocked to see satay sliced to thiny bits, cooked nd wrapped. Phuii!!!
Wantan noodles. Rather average serving from Tong Aik #01-09. One of the few Chinese stalls open for breakfast on a Sunday morning
Try the minced meat noodles and nasi lemak. One of my favorite stalls sells Hokkien mee at night, next to the Western food stall.
The yeo ji mee sua: IMBA.
The minced meat noodles is one of the best I've ever had! Only $3 for a big bowl! =)
Try Aliff's Nasi Lemak!
Must try Mandarin chicken rice & feet no regrets
Mee sua - Taiwan style. Western food - corner stall
添南欣 mince pork Mee, must try!
The foods are nice here. Weekends will be pretty pack.
try Quan Xing Spicy Prawn Cracker #01-25 (Chinese rojak )
Do not buy the large cup of sugarcane. Tried finishing the large cup and refilling it with the small, same amount.
MEE SUA FRIED OYSTER BBQ CHICKEN WINGS YAS

Muz try the pig liver mee sua and claypot rice ! Yums .
美美铁板烧鱼（M. M. B.B.Q. Fish) is a must try if u love chilli food!~
Hong kong mei mei (beside seng kee) - potato leaves is amazing, black bean fish is yum.
The pig mee sua is average. But the meat is really very tender and soft, recommended for patients.
The mee sua is nice!
Claypot chicken rice is nice!
Yummy Nasi Lemak stall here - go for Aliff Nasi Lemak
Morning: Must try: Char Kway. Afternoon: must try: nasi lemak. Evening: must try: MEE sua
Try the Chong pang chicken wings and satay ! Yummyyyy ^-^ 
What's nice abt the wantan mee over here?? It's normal to me..
I feel so tired. Oh wait, everyday I feel tired -.-

bar chor mee : shiok!
Mee sua a must have!
Having Song Chew Lor Mee, guess that's where my dad always buy me for bf! Try it!
He Cheng cafe, the Teh -O ice lemon tea was well mixed.
Enjoyed TeoChew Fishball 潮洲鱼丸
511 mee sua FTW !
the pisang goreng vy cripy n yummy
Must eat the bak chor mee. (Minced meat noodles). Better than block 85. Don't know what they put in their soup man. Can request for bigger bowl. Another must try is the seng kee mee sua. Yum.
Nur Janatun Naim's spring chicken, fish and chips and satay are superb!!! Add tat wif their home made chilli sauce... XD
The Hotplate Stingray is fantastic! Spicy yet fragrant with dried prawns. The stingray is grilled just nice & super juicy!
The Chong pang satay is very nice! 8/10THE BBQ chicken wing was tender and the texture was good. Chilli was spicy !
Sinaran cahaya fried chicken rice and janatun fish and chips and roti marvellous!!!!!! Yummy!!!!
腰子面线，claypot 伊面，western food!!! all thumbs up !!!
Thumb up for claypot rice for stall Hong Kong Mei Mei.. Superb delicious!! Much nice than famous geylang claypot rice
The SKBCHS Store sells good food. Must Try! :D
Try their japanese food there. Quite nice
Try the M M BBQ fish stall .
Stingray here is simply delicious always saw half of the market having it😕 its a must try
Try Aliff Nasi Lemak!!
The BCM stall shouts "35mins wait hor". Wa sorry to bother you, bye!
Must try the kidney mee suah soup and "Wu Xiang"
潮州魚粥！great fish soup.
The Ba Chor Mee Is Super Nice!
If kway chap is your thing, then the food stall to check out here is the Hougang Kway Chap Stall at #01-26.
Mee sua + stingray + barbecue chicken wing + sugarcane = shiok!!!!!
Seafood kway teow, fried rice seafood, beef n seafood hor fun n even the Maggie soup fm the Malay stall facing the road are superb.  Must try stall when u are here.
Zhi Char corner stall must try!
love the fish-ball noodle here=] yum yum
Best wu Xiang !
Seng kee mee suah is terrrrific!

U will like the food at there

Minced Pork Noodle is the best ! Much better than famous Bedok Blk 85 market food fare

Mee sua is a must have I'm so craving for it now!
Try the minced pork noodle here! Unit #01-10! Must-try!
The foods are nice, try any stalls also no regret. Very famous is the mee suan.
Minced meat noodles for $3 at night is to die for!!!

so missing thereT^T
The bak chor mee ! My fav
Xi Wang bak kut teh fail ! Pls do not try.. Taste very bland. Waste my money !

Kway chap is good! The BBQ food also sibei shiok bodoh
Chicken chop at jet wings is quite good. Crisp skin, light soya dressing.
E roti john cheese at sri janatun is a killa! Its a must to try!
The kidney mee sua soup at #01-31/32 is awesome!
Oyster omelettes here are unbeatable. :D
Best BBQ chicken wings!!
Most delicious stingray ever!
Love the claypot chicken rice here
Tried it before. Took 3 items and was charged $4.50.anchovies, peanuts & cucumber was charged separately. Was wondering isn't Nasi lemak comes with those. The 1st & last!
Must try pig kidney mee suan, claypot pork, veg with mushroom, steam fish, soup etc... Same stall. U won't regret. Plus the western food also not bad too.
Claypot. The soup is delicious and healthy.
Bak chor mee & mee sua are not to be missed : )
Tong aik wanton noodles is good. Opens on morning only
Morning : Nasi Lemak or Fish Soup .. Night: Mee sua
